content.description: Super fun pockets. Thin crux around the 3rd or 4th bolt
content.location: Just right of the prominent but short dihedral that starts the 12a

content.description: This route would probably be good, if it were cleaned. As it stands now, expect to pull stuff off it. Your belayer should stand well off to the side.
content.location: 1st route right of Ignorance is bliss.

content.description: Climb past the 2 new, and 2 old bolts that mark the start of The Great Tradition, then trend right. The crux is the cool flake feature down low
content.location: Clip the 4 bolts marking the start of the prominent crack route, then continue up the bolt line.

content.description: The crux is the mid route grey slopers. The bottom of the route goes over a small sloping ledge after a high 1st bolt.
content.location: The bolted line just left of the bolted finger crack (Sam's crack), on the right hand of the lower picnic table rock.

content.description: Climb the highly feature rock, left of the black huecos of The Leopard, also 10B.
content.location: The cleanish, brown colored central line, 2 routes left of the prominent crack of "The Great Tradition".

content.description: The crux is getting established on the face right of the dihedral. Fun slab route
content.location: The right hand route starting from the base of the large pine, on the right hand side of the crag.

content.description: This route is slightly below the left skyline of the formation as seen from the parking area and is best done in three pitches.

climbs.name: The Second Joy of My Life

content.description: The appealing slab to the right of the prominent pillar which hosts the amazing route Dr. Ceuse. Cruise past some nice holds and a rad hueco-esque feature. Rap off at a chain anchor.

climbs.name: Sam's Crack
climbs.fa: October 14' Sam Carter, Equipped by Richard Labelle

content.description: A less than vertical seam/crack with a balanced thought provoking crux near the top
content.location: On the same side of the canyon as Ceuse, but farther down canyon and right off the dirt road. An obvious left leaning crack

content.description: Begins on very featured mossy horizontal flakes and ascends to the large grassy ledge, then continues off the ledge to the anchors above.
content.location: A two tiered route very near and to the right of Sam's Crack and to the left of the Ceuse Rocks.

content.description: Start in the chimney on the right side. Climb up the face and step right onto the arÃªte. Thoughtful moves the res of the way will keep your attention all the way to the chains.
Named for the big spots of black lichen, this climb is cruxy thin edging on low angle rock. The top anchors are above a ledge about 15' below the summit.
content.location: This line goes up the black huecos.

content.description: 3 bolts on the lower slab lead into a gear-protected dihedral above. Lay-back and face climb up the dihedral until you reach the 4th bolt which protects a few moves over a small bulge to anchors. Named after the wild turkey that cratered in my windshield minutes after leaving Northrup Canyon.. Shady until early afternoon.
After the second bolt, climb the ramps on the left side of the main lower wall. Then the route goes straight up through technical terrain.
content.location: Almost the last route to the left before entering the trees to access Jive Turkey and the unnamed slab.

content.description:
Amazing exposure up a pillar with good protection and decent quality rock. 15 bolts and a few long slings to help with rope drag.

Climb up Jugoslavia for 8 bolts and traverse left to the pillar, put a long sling on the 8th bolt and continue on for 7 more bolts.
content.protection: 15 bolts and a few long slings to help with rope drag.
content.location: Look up at Picnic Table Rock and find the obvious Pillar up high. It starts at the bottom of the chimney and then traverses left onto the pillar climbing the arete.

climbs.name: Could you learn to love me

content.description: Crux in the light colored dish down low. This route needs cleaning
content.location: Thin start in the short, prominent dihedral
